The  senior men and women’s 3×3 teams and the under 18 boys and girls have commenced camping at the Package B of the National Stadium, Abuja  in preparation for the 2019 3×3 FIBA Africa Nations Cup (AFCON) which comes up in Kampala, Uganda from November 7 to 11. Kano Pillars duo of Okoh Lucky Subel and Godwin David were invited alongside Abuchi Ibe Agu and Anyaoha Wisdom. Koko Victor Antony and Ndibe Emmanuel complete the list of invited players for the camping which opened on Sunday, 15 September. They hope to improve on the Bronze won in the 2018 edition. First Bank’s Okoro Ifunanya earned another call up to camp alongside team mates , Kelani Sumbo  and Umeh Gloria. Agbotan Success, Okah Chinwe Hope and Theresa Mac-Dangosu complete the list of players invited for the women’s team. The U18 boys team include Oyebanji Mustapha, Odufuwa Kanyinsola, David Adetutu, Emmanuel James, Godwin Peace,  Samaila Antibas, Michael Ayodele, Oyedokun Olamilekan and Akomolafe Oyekanmi. The U18 girls comprise Onuorah Chika, Agba Agatha, Joseph Godgift, Ezebilo Grace Gbihi Cynthia and Okeke Chidinma  who were all invited after a strong showing at the recently concluded second phase of the Zenith Women Basketball League. Linda Adejoh, Omaga Olivia, Ubi Majomary and Nwachukwu Ifunanya complete the list of 10 players invited to the U18 girls camp. Acha Chris, Christopher Okoh, Juliana Akhere and Nnorom Mark will be in charge of the teams while Simon Evbuoman has been picked as the accompanying referee.